WEBVTT

00:01.043 --> 00:02.419
♪♪

00:02.419 --> 00:04.254
Hey, Jimmy.
What's up?

00:04.254 --> 00:06.131
Good.

00:06.131 --> 00:08.634
Good.

00:08.634 --> 00:12.095
If I ‐‐ like ‐‐ No.
Okay.

00:14.139 --> 00:17.142
Do you have trouble talking to
Kenneth when JJ's not around?

00:17.142 --> 00:18.685
You'd think by now,
I'd have something to say

00:18.685 --> 00:19.937
to the guy,
but it's always awkward.

00:19.937 --> 00:21.188
Never been a problem
for me.

00:21.188 --> 00:23.023
Morning, Maya.
Good morning, Kenneth.

00:23.023 --> 00:24.441
How do you do that?

00:24.441 --> 00:26.652
Hey, someone's birthday
coming up?

00:26.652 --> 00:28.862
It's Dylan's.
I throw the best parties.

00:28.862 --> 00:31.448
I have an uncanny ability to get
inside the mind‐set of a child.

00:31.448 --> 00:32.824
If only
you could get <i>out.</i>

00:32.824 --> 00:34.159
I've told you, Ray ‐‐

00:34.159 --> 00:36.370
No walking into rooms
to deliver zingers.

00:36.370 --> 00:38.622
Every year,
I throw her a surprise party.

00:38.622 --> 00:39.915
Doesn't that stop
being surprising?

00:39.915 --> 00:40.999
Not the way I do it.

00:40.999 --> 00:43.335
Dylan, we're not going
for ice cream

00:43.335 --> 00:46.088
until you've cleaned up
all your outside toys.

00:46.088 --> 00:48.799
All: Surprise!

00:48.799 --> 00:51.218
Just need to stop
in the bathroom.

00:51.218 --> 00:53.845
All: Surprise!

00:53.845 --> 00:56.014
What's the hold‐up?!
Move!

00:56.014 --> 00:56.807
[ Horn honks ]

00:56.807 --> 00:59.559
All: Surprise!

00:59.559 --> 01:01.979
And this is
the big one ‐‐ 13.

01:01.979 --> 01:03.730
This blowout will be
the stuff of legend.

01:03.730 --> 01:05.357
In nine months' time,
children will be born

01:05.357 --> 01:07.317
with the name
"Dylan's Party."

01:07.317 --> 01:08.902
Hey, Mom,
I was actually thinking

01:08.902 --> 01:10.445
we could skip the party
this year.

01:10.445 --> 01:13.156
You know, we've had a nice run.
Just ‐‐ I think I'm good.

01:13.156 --> 01:14.283
Thanks.

01:16.493 --> 01:17.995
Surprise.

01:22.040 --> 01:23.458
Dylan, stop.

01:23.458 --> 01:25.586
Why don't you want
a surprise party?

01:25.586 --> 01:27.713
Kids just aren't really doing
that kind of stuff anymore.

01:27.713 --> 01:29.923
I thought I would just
hang out with my friends
at the mall or something.

01:29.923 --> 01:32.092
Maybe you and I can do
something separate?

01:32.092 --> 01:34.344
Oh, okay.
If ‐‐ If that's what you want.

01:34.344 --> 01:35.804
Great.

01:35.804 --> 01:38.015
And another
DiMeo family tradition

01:38.015 --> 01:39.808
goes the way
of "Nightly Bible Hour."

01:41.143 --> 01:43.020
[ Door opens ]
Right ‐‐
Dylan's birthday.

01:43.020 --> 01:45.314
I forgot.
[ Door closes ]

01:45.314 --> 01:47.065
"Get her a gift
together?"

01:47.065 --> 01:48.275
That's a great idea.

01:48.275 --> 01:49.735
But if it's from
both of us,

01:49.735 --> 01:51.069
it needs to be
really thoughtful ‐‐

01:51.069 --> 01:53.071
not just the first thing
that pops up in our heads.

01:53.071 --> 01:55.365
S‐N ‐‐ "Sneakers."
Sure. Fine.

01:55.365 --> 01:57.743
Enough torturing ourselves.
Let's go get Mom to drive us.

01:59.286 --> 02:01.580
Hey, Mom, JJ and I need
to go to the sneaker store

02:01.580 --> 02:02.914
to get Dylan's present.

02:02.914 --> 02:04.166
Alone?

02:04.166 --> 02:07.127
But you've never gone out
just the two of you bef‐‐

02:07.127 --> 02:08.295
What is happening today?

02:08.295 --> 02:09.504
Actually, I meant ‐‐

02:09.504 --> 02:10.881
My children don't need me
anymore.

02:10.881 --> 02:13.258
I believe it's time
to start phase 2 of my life ‐‐

02:13.258 --> 02:15.677
feeding pigeons braless
in the park

02:15.677 --> 02:17.262
while solving
old murder cases.

02:17.262 --> 02:19.556
[ Sighs ] Right. Well,
just tell me when you leave.

02:19.556 --> 02:21.808
Ray, you be careful. You're
responsible for your brother.

02:21.808 --> 02:23.560
I'll take care of him.

02:23.560 --> 02:24.770
Come on.

02:24.770 --> 02:25.937
Ugh!

02:25.937 --> 02:28.065
I'm just gonna leave you two
to it.

02:28.065 --> 02:30.067
What two?

02:30.067 --> 02:31.318
'Sup?

02:31.318 --> 02:33.904
Fantastic. Thanks.

02:33.904 --> 02:36.281
♪ Hold me close,
don't ever...♪

02:36.281 --> 02:38.742
Mmm! Chicken Parm?
My favorite.

02:38.742 --> 02:41.620
And you opened
the Goldschlager.

02:41.620 --> 02:43.830
I like
where this is going!

02:43.830 --> 02:46.458
♪ Is all I ever ♪
Wait a second.

02:46.458 --> 02:48.085
Is this the "Big Eighties
Power Ballads" CD?

02:48.085 --> 02:50.003
Mm‐hmm.

02:50.003 --> 02:51.922
No! We are not
having another child!

02:51.922 --> 02:54.424
Oh, no, no, no.
That's not what this is...

02:54.424 --> 02:56.385
Stud.
Unh‐unh!

02:56.385 --> 02:58.929
I know all your moves ‐‐
drinks that taste like college,

02:58.929 --> 03:01.556
baby‐making music
sung by men with your hair.

03:01.556 --> 03:04.184
Yeah ‐‐
All right, you got me!

03:04.184 --> 03:05.268
Dylan is broken!

03:05.268 --> 03:06.520
We need to make
another person

03:06.520 --> 03:07.646
who will love me
unconditionally.

03:07.646 --> 03:09.481
<i>I</i> love you unconditionally.

03:09.481 --> 03:11.316
Then make me a baby!
Maya!

03:11.316 --> 03:13.902
Dylan is my buddy
and she is my baby,

03:13.902 --> 03:15.237
and she doesn't want me
hanging around her friends,

03:15.237 --> 03:18.782
which is ridiculous,
because I am the cool mom.

03:18.782 --> 03:21.243
I am the coolest mom
in town.

03:21.243 --> 03:22.911
That would be
a sad pageant.

03:22.911 --> 03:27.249
Look, Dylan is growing
and making decisions

03:27.249 --> 03:28.959
because
we did our job right.

03:28.959 --> 03:32.671
If this is what she wants,
we got to respect that.

03:32.671 --> 03:35.590
So, once again,
the problem is

03:35.590 --> 03:37.175
that we're too good
at parenting.

03:37.175 --> 03:38.009
Exactly.

03:38.009 --> 03:39.886
Okay, okay. Yeah.
Yeah.

03:39.886 --> 03:41.263
So, no baby.

03:41.263 --> 03:43.473
Okay.

03:43.473 --> 03:45.308
Okay.

03:45.308 --> 03:48.478
You know what ‐‐ I'm gonna
turn off the CD just to be safe.

03:48.478 --> 03:51.189
[ Video game beeping ]

03:52.607 --> 03:54.693
All right, all right!
What?

03:56.236 --> 03:58.738
S ‐‐ "Store time."

03:58.738 --> 04:00.073
Later.
I want to finish this.

04:01.408 --> 04:02.659
Dad said I'm in charge.

04:04.494 --> 04:06.580
"We're going now."

04:06.580 --> 04:08.707
Uh, I don't think we are,

04:08.707 --> 04:10.167
unless you plan on going
yourself.

04:16.381 --> 04:18.508
[ Scoffs ]
Telling me when to go.

04:18.508 --> 04:19.926
Who's in charge?

04:19.926 --> 04:22.220
<i>Ray's</i> in charge, B‐word.

04:22.220 --> 04:23.472
♪♪

04:23.472 --> 04:25.265
Mm. Yeah. Hm.

04:25.265 --> 04:27.642
[ Cellphone chimes ]

04:27.642 --> 04:30.228
Ugh!
Aah! Man, I can't
take it anymore.

04:30.228 --> 04:31.646
This is so awkward.

04:31.646 --> 04:33.482
I never have anything
to say to you.

04:33.482 --> 04:35.650
You feel that? I feel that, too.
Why didn't you say anything?

04:35.650 --> 04:37.194
I want to,
but then I look up,

04:37.194 --> 04:39.154
and you're all there,
making me say nothing.

04:39.154 --> 04:40.739
This is good. It's out there,
and we can fix it.

04:40.739 --> 04:42.073
Yeah, okay.

04:42.073 --> 04:43.742
There must be something
that we have in common.

04:43.742 --> 04:45.327
Yeah!

04:50.248 --> 04:52.083
You...

04:52.083 --> 04:55.212
Uh...Well ‐‐ well,
what do guys talk about?

04:55.212 --> 04:56.755
Uh...babes.

04:56.755 --> 04:58.340
Sure! Babes.

04:58.340 --> 04:59.216
Let's talk about those.

04:59.216 --> 05:00.425
Yeah.
Yeah!

05:00.425 --> 05:03.470
So, Kenneth...

05:03.470 --> 05:05.263
you, like, a butt guy,
or...?

05:07.682 --> 05:09.351
L‐Let's talk about
something else.

05:09.351 --> 05:10.769
<i>Anything</i> else, really.
Yeah.

05:10.769 --> 05:11.978
All right, JJ, let's go.

05:13.522 --> 05:15.106
JJ?

05:15.106 --> 05:16.942
JJ?

05:16.942 --> 05:18.276
JJ, are you in here?

05:18.276 --> 05:20.111
Where the heck did he go?

05:20.111 --> 05:22.948
♪♪

05:24.866 --> 05:25.951
Hi!

05:30.539 --> 05:33.291
Are you sure that's all you want
for your birthday, darling ‐‐

05:33.291 --> 05:34.459
just the two of us?

05:34.459 --> 05:36.378
Yeah. I'll see my friends
tomorrow.

05:36.378 --> 05:38.255
Ohh. If you say so.

05:38.255 --> 05:40.632
All: Surprise!

05:41.967 --> 05:43.969
Eh?
I said I didn't want this.

05:43.969 --> 05:45.595
I know, but I'd already ordered
the fake wall.

05:50.016 --> 05:51.142
Mom, I told you I d‐‐
I know ‐‐ you wanted

05:51.142 --> 05:52.602
to do something separate
with your friends.

05:52.602 --> 05:53.770
But please,
just give me a chance

05:53.770 --> 05:55.063
to show you how much fun
I can make for you all.

05:55.063 --> 05:56.982
Go on ‐‐ look over there.
What do you see?

05:56.982 --> 05:58.275
My friends?
No. Boring.

05:58.275 --> 06:00.110
Move over, friends.

06:00.110 --> 06:01.611
Look at that. Huh?

06:01.611 --> 06:03.321
The cool kids.

06:03.321 --> 06:05.073
I got the coolest girl
in your grade ‐‐ Elle McAdams.

06:05.073 --> 06:06.533
'Sup, Dyl?

06:06.533 --> 06:08.827
Don't just stand there... Dyl.
Tell her "'sup."

06:10.328 --> 06:12.372
Wha‐‐ Are you still here?
Where's JJ?

06:12.372 --> 06:13.748
Did he go without you?

06:13.748 --> 06:15.083
[ Chuckles ]
[ Laughs nervously ]

06:15.083 --> 06:17.377
There's a little bit of truth
in every joke,

06:17.377 --> 06:18.670
but not that one.

06:18.670 --> 06:19.963
Coming, JJ!

06:19.963 --> 06:23.258
I see you in that safe place
where you are.

06:23.258 --> 06:24.718
[ Door closes ]

06:24.718 --> 06:27.345
Now, theme ‐‐
I thought long and hard,

06:27.345 --> 06:29.180
and obviously,
there is one thing

06:29.180 --> 06:31.474
that you care about
more than anything else.

06:31.474 --> 06:33.018
Winning.
Winning.

06:33.018 --> 06:35.812
So note the decor ‐‐
all your trophies and ribbons,

06:35.812 --> 06:38.940
you photoshopped
into iconic images of victory,

06:38.940 --> 06:42.360
including the monument to you
you've always wanted.

06:42.360 --> 06:44.070
You made Mount Crushmore?

06:44.070 --> 06:45.697
I did.

06:45.697 --> 06:48.408
Darling, I got all these games
for you all to play.

06:48.408 --> 06:50.619
[ Whispering ] I can totally rig
anything for you to win.

06:53.246 --> 06:54.456
You mean
you didn't already?

06:55.373 --> 06:57.626
♪♪

07:09.429 --> 07:12.057
Okay, who's got the laser?

07:12.057 --> 07:13.600
Off my bus now!

07:17.228 --> 07:18.772
Hey.

07:18.772 --> 07:20.398
We're gonna find
a thing we have in common.

07:20.398 --> 07:22.025
I made a list.

07:22.025 --> 07:25.028
Eugh. Strike one.
I'm not really a big lists guy.

07:25.028 --> 07:27.030
But I ‐‐
I spent a half ‐‐

07:27.030 --> 07:29.616
How about... music?

07:29.616 --> 07:31.242
Uh...I love music.

07:31.242 --> 07:33.161
Uh, do you like
The Ramones?

07:33.161 --> 07:34.329
You know the Ramones?

07:34.329 --> 07:35.789
Know?
I <i>love</i> The Ramones.

07:35.789 --> 07:36.915
[ Laughs ] Yeah?

07:36.915 --> 07:38.333
I live next door to them.

07:38.333 --> 07:40.085
Man, they are fat!

07:40.085 --> 07:41.795
Oh, the parents,
the kids ‐‐ blech!

07:41.795 --> 07:44.005
I‐I didn't know
they played music.

07:44.005 --> 07:45.632
Wh‐‐ What are we talking about?
What just happened?

07:46.424 --> 07:47.258
Fwoom.

07:48.551 --> 07:50.345
[ Sighs ]

07:50.345 --> 07:52.639
Huh. What's that?
A... brisket?

07:52.639 --> 07:54.557
You know it.
Check out that marbling.

07:54.557 --> 07:55.767
Oh, I was checking out
that marbling

07:55.767 --> 07:57.143
and that beautiful fat cap.
Fat cap.

07:58.978 --> 08:00.188
You're a barbecue guy?

08:00.188 --> 08:01.690
<i>You're</i> a barbecue guy.
Yeah!

08:01.690 --> 08:02.941
We're barbecue guys.
We have a thing.

08:02.941 --> 08:04.275
We got a thing!

08:04.275 --> 08:05.735
I'm gonna show you my setup.
We've got a thing.

08:05.735 --> 08:06.820
♪ We got a thing! ♪

08:06.820 --> 08:09.364
♪ We got a thing!
We got a thing! ♪

08:09.364 --> 08:11.157
And chanting, too!

08:11.157 --> 08:13.451
♪ We got two things!
We got two things! ♪

08:13.451 --> 08:15.412
[ Up‐tempo guitar music plays ]

08:36.641 --> 08:39.394
[ Tires screech, horns blare ]

08:41.938 --> 08:44.107
[ Indistinct conversations ]

08:44.107 --> 08:46.943
[ Laughter ]

08:47.902 --> 08:49.195
[ Cheering ]

08:49.195 --> 08:50.447
Oh, my goodness!

08:50.447 --> 08:52.949
Now, I know
we're all having a blast,

08:52.949 --> 08:56.745
but what could make this party
even bloody better?

08:56.745 --> 08:58.747
Hang on to your hormones,
girls,

08:58.747 --> 09:04.502
'cause this is about to become
your first boy/girl party!

09:04.502 --> 09:07.213
[ Dance music plays ]

09:07.213 --> 09:09.215
Whoa.

09:09.215 --> 09:11.342
What is that walking?
Don't do that.

09:11.342 --> 09:12.260
I didn't tell them
to do that.

09:12.260 --> 09:14.220
Oh, no. Logan's here?

09:14.220 --> 09:16.347
You better believe it,
and he is dressed to impress.

09:16.347 --> 09:18.892
Go on ‐‐
give us a twirl, Logan.

09:18.892 --> 09:20.643
That felt bad.
I won't do that again.

09:22.729 --> 09:24.564
Hi. I'm loo‐‐
I'm looking for my brother.

09:24.564 --> 09:26.316
We were supposed to meet up
at this store.

09:26.316 --> 09:27.317
What's he look like?

09:27.317 --> 09:28.526
16, brown hair ‐‐

09:28.526 --> 09:29.694
They're <i>all</i> 16
with brown hair.

09:29.694 --> 09:31.488
Uh, he uses
a wheelchair, he ‐‐

09:31.488 --> 09:33.448
Really? And you didn't
just say <i>that?</i>

09:33.448 --> 09:35.241
Should I have?
Not at all.

09:35.241 --> 09:37.118
I think it's really cool that
you don't define him that way.

09:37.118 --> 09:38.244
I mean, why lead
with "wheelchair"?

09:38.244 --> 09:39.913
He's so much more
than that.

09:39.913 --> 09:41.081
You're probably
the right guy to ask ‐‐

09:41.081 --> 09:44.125
Is the correct term
"disabled" or "special needs"?

09:44.125 --> 09:45.919
Well, there are
a lot of opinions ‐‐

09:45.919 --> 09:47.629
I've also heard
"differently abled."

09:47.629 --> 09:49.422
Okay, I really need
to find him.

09:49.422 --> 09:50.840
How long ago was he here?

09:50.840 --> 09:53.134
I have not seen anyone
in a wheelchair.

09:53.134 --> 09:55.929
Then why are we having
this conversation?

09:55.929 --> 09:58.598
You know, we have another store
over at the mall.

09:59.891 --> 10:02.227
Hey. It's Kirk
over at Maple Avenue.

10:02.227 --> 10:04.813
Yeah, you seen a kid there,
brown hair, about 16,

10:04.813 --> 10:06.981
uses a wheelchair?

10:06.981 --> 10:08.775
Actually,
I <i>don't</i> define him that way.

10:08.775 --> 10:10.652
[ Sighs ]
I appreciate that you share
the sensitivity.

10:10.652 --> 10:11.861
Have we met?

10:11.861 --> 10:13.947
We should get the stores
together more often.

10:15.365 --> 10:16.783
There she is.

10:17.992 --> 10:18.993
What?

10:18.993 --> 10:20.662
[ Sighs ] This...

10:20.662 --> 10:21.663
[ Scoffs ]

10:21.663 --> 10:23.456
...is a <i>gas</i> grill.

10:23.456 --> 10:25.750
No.
Not a charcoal snob.

10:25.750 --> 10:28.878
Jimmy, you got to go charcoal
if you want real barbecue.

10:28.878 --> 10:30.421
Dude, that flavor!

10:30.421 --> 10:32.423
The flavor
doesn't come from charcoal.

10:32.423 --> 10:33.883
It comes
from the drippings.

10:33.883 --> 10:35.885
They hit the heat source,
and ‐‐ poof ‐‐ aroma!

10:35.885 --> 10:37.220
"Poof"?
Poof!

10:37.220 --> 10:38.638
Oh. Okay.
You know what?

10:38.638 --> 10:40.098
I don't want to overreact
or anything,

10:40.098 --> 10:41.683
but tell JJ
it's been real!

10:42.851 --> 10:44.477
Okay,
you feel so strong?

10:44.477 --> 10:45.728
You go get <i>your</i> grill.

10:45.728 --> 10:47.021
We'll have ourselves
a little taste test.

10:47.021 --> 10:48.565
It is on!
It's on!

10:48.565 --> 10:51.317
Time of death ‐‐ 3:49.

10:51.317 --> 10:53.194
I'm referring
to our thing!

10:53.194 --> 10:54.028
Yeah.

10:59.325 --> 11:01.619
[ Dog barks ]
Hey, hey, hey! No, no!

11:01.619 --> 11:03.413
It's your laser dot.

11:03.413 --> 11:05.248
He loves them.
They're delicious.

11:05.248 --> 11:07.500
[ Both laugh ]

11:07.500 --> 11:08.585
No dogs allowed, ma'am.

11:08.585 --> 11:09.502
Ohh!

11:12.130 --> 11:16.217
"This...is...my S‐E‐R ‐‐

11:16.217 --> 11:17.427
service dog."

11:17.427 --> 11:20.221
Oh. I'm sorry, sir.
My mistake.

11:20.221 --> 11:22.432
That was so kind of you.

11:22.432 --> 11:24.934
Isn't that nice, sweetie?
Yes!

11:24.934 --> 11:26.019
[ Dog barking ]

11:26.019 --> 11:27.979
Actually,
you should probably go.

11:27.979 --> 11:30.064
He really has no business
being here.

11:30.064 --> 11:32.108
[ Barking continues ]

11:34.485 --> 11:36.070
Yes! I win!

11:36.070 --> 11:37.864
Loser! Loser! Loser!

11:37.864 --> 11:39.991
We're doing a jigsaw puzzle
together.

11:39.991 --> 11:41.326
There's no winners.

11:41.326 --> 11:42.785
Spoken like a true loser.

11:44.495 --> 11:46.581
Mom.
What are you doing?

11:46.581 --> 11:48.291
Oh, I'm helping Elle.

11:48.291 --> 11:50.418
She's trying to decide whether
she and Logan have a future.

11:50.418 --> 11:53.838
Last week, I asked him
if we were on a sinking ship,

11:53.838 --> 11:56.633
and he had the choice,
would he save his family or me?

11:56.633 --> 11:58.218
[ Voice breaking ]
And he said he wasn't sure.

11:58.218 --> 11:59.594
He wasn't sure.

11:59.594 --> 12:02.222
And after you gave him
the best two weeks of your life.

12:02.222 --> 12:05.099
Look, Mom ‐‐
Oh, darling, I'm not
embarrassing you. I promise.

12:05.099 --> 12:06.434
No ‐‐
Elle thinks I'm cool.
Don't you, Elle?

12:06.434 --> 12:07.936
You're cooler
than either of my moms.

12:07.936 --> 12:09.395
I'd tell them,
but they're at Coachella.

12:09.395 --> 12:10.813
Do you hear that, Dylan?

12:10.813 --> 12:12.982
I'm cooler
than Coachella lesbians.

12:12.982 --> 12:15.735
[ Panting ]

12:15.735 --> 12:16.986
[ Cellphone rings ]

12:16.986 --> 12:17.987
Oh, no!

12:17.987 --> 12:18.988
[ Cellphone beeps ]

12:18.988 --> 12:20.156
Hi, Mom.

12:20.156 --> 12:23.076
Hi, Ray. Just making sure
you two are all right.

12:23.076 --> 12:25.370
Yep. I'm fine.
So's JJ.

12:25.370 --> 12:27.914
He can tell you himself.

12:27.914 --> 12:29.791
<i>"I'm... fine."</i>

12:29.791 --> 12:31.918
Okay, well,
take good care of him.

12:31.918 --> 12:33.836
[ Cellphone beeps ]

12:33.836 --> 12:37.131
♪♪

12:37.131 --> 12:38.800
JJ!

12:38.800 --> 12:40.426
JJ! There you are!

12:40.426 --> 12:41.552
What are you doing?!

12:41.552 --> 12:44.639
"Getting Dylan's shoes
without you."

12:44.639 --> 12:46.307
I can't believe you!

12:46.307 --> 12:48.935
Stop smiling!
This is serious.

12:48.935 --> 12:50.770
I'm responsible for you.

12:52.939 --> 12:55.275
"Who wants that?

12:55.275 --> 12:56.567
I'm the big brother.

12:56.567 --> 12:59.696
<i>I</i> should take care of <i>you."</i>

13:02.532 --> 13:05.076
Okay. Heavy.

13:05.076 --> 13:06.828
Not equipped for that
at all.

13:07.996 --> 13:09.622
[ Sighs ] We came here
to get the shoes.

13:09.622 --> 13:11.624
Now let's go get the shoes.

13:11.624 --> 13:13.001
The store closes in,
like ‐‐

13:13.001 --> 13:14.877
Oh, no!
Like, one minute!

13:14.877 --> 13:16.462
And the elevators
are all the way down there.

13:16.462 --> 13:17.672
All right, come on!
Let's go!

13:22.260 --> 13:23.720
"Just go."

13:23.720 --> 13:24.554
Really?

13:25.972 --> 13:27.265
"I had my fun."

13:32.103 --> 13:33.438
[ Sizzling ]

13:33.438 --> 13:34.355
[ Exhales deeply ]

13:34.355 --> 13:35.481
Moment of truth.

13:36.482 --> 13:37.525
Hm.

13:40.320 --> 13:41.988
Well?
Mm!

13:43.865 --> 13:45.533
I can't do this
to my stomach.

13:45.533 --> 13:47.285
Maybe you should just
stick to saying things

13:47.285 --> 13:48.870
my son makes you say.

13:48.870 --> 13:50.955
[ Laughing ] Oh!
The gloves are off, huh?

13:50.955 --> 13:52.707
I can see how your meat
didn't turn out,

13:52.707 --> 13:54.417
without Maya
telling you what to do.

13:54.417 --> 13:55.376
Ohh!

13:55.376 --> 13:56.419
You're totally qualified

13:56.419 --> 13:57.795
to give an opinion
about a marriage

13:57.795 --> 13:59.464
because you've had
so many of them.

13:59.464 --> 14:01.090
At least I know
when something's done.

14:01.090 --> 14:02.091
Ha!
Speaking of which...

14:02.091 --> 14:03.593
Mm.
Hm?

14:04.719 --> 14:06.345
Hm.

14:06.345 --> 14:08.890
Fun fact ‐‐ You're not actually
supposed to <i>eat</i> the charcoal.

14:08.890 --> 14:10.558
Okay. So, I can see
it's a stalemate.

14:10.558 --> 14:11.476
Mm.

14:11.476 --> 14:12.727
You know
what'll settle this?

14:12.727 --> 14:14.812
Swords.
No, man. Taste testers.

14:14.812 --> 14:16.022
Okay, fine.
[ Chuckles ]

14:16.022 --> 14:18.316
But if that doesn't decide it,
we go swords.

14:18.316 --> 14:21.652
[ Indistinct shouting ]

14:21.652 --> 14:22.737
Yes!
[ Cheering ]

14:22.737 --> 14:24.739
Yes! Oh, my gosh! Mom!
Mom, did you see that?

14:24.739 --> 14:26.157
I beat Bryce Thomas!

14:26.157 --> 14:27.492
He does steroids!

14:27.492 --> 14:28.951
Mom, did you ‐‐

14:28.951 --> 14:30.953
Oh, get a room,
you two!

14:30.953 --> 14:33.706
Elle has a problem.
She wanted me.

14:33.706 --> 14:35.500
It's not my fault
I have a big heart

14:35.500 --> 14:36.918
and that today's teens
sense

14:36.918 --> 14:38.878
I'm tuned
to their emotions and issues.

14:38.878 --> 14:40.254
Yeah, well,
not <i>this</i> teen.

14:40.254 --> 14:41.881
I told you
I didn't want a party.

14:41.881 --> 14:44.092
Yeah, but it's great.
You're having fun.

14:44.092 --> 14:45.927
Yeah, until you spent
the whole time talking to Elle.

14:45.927 --> 14:48.012
Elle is not bothered by me.
Are you, Elle?

14:48.012 --> 14:49.388
[ Sobbing ] No!

14:49.388 --> 14:50.973
Yeah, all right, all right,
all right. Thank you.

14:50.973 --> 14:53.309
Believe it or not, your mom
is not some lame embarrassment.

14:53.309 --> 14:54.977
You think
I don't know that?

14:54.977 --> 14:58.106
You're freaking amazing.
That's the problem.

14:58.106 --> 14:59.899
I didn't want a party
because I didn't want

14:59.899 --> 15:01.651
to have to share you
with these dweebs.

15:01.651 --> 15:03.236
That's why you're upset?

15:03.236 --> 15:05.655
Darling, I had no idea.

15:07.865 --> 15:08.783
"Dweebs"?

15:08.783 --> 15:10.201
Can a dweeb do this?

15:11.786 --> 15:13.496
[ Sobbing ]

15:13.496 --> 15:14.580
Yeah. Elle wants
to see other people.

15:18.334 --> 15:20.628
You want to be with me?

15:20.628 --> 15:21.712
Who wouldn't?

15:21.712 --> 15:23.589
You're the coolest mom
in town.

15:23.589 --> 15:25.299
Well, darling, you're preaching
to the choir.

15:25.299 --> 15:26.759
A <i>great</i> choir.

15:26.759 --> 15:27.927
I do sing very well.

15:29.554 --> 15:32.306
I had no idea
you wanted me to yourself.

15:32.306 --> 15:35.893
Good. I don't want you
worrying about what I want.

15:35.893 --> 15:37.937
Then there's always
someone cutting me in line.

15:37.937 --> 15:39.438
JJ ‐‐ I get that.

15:39.438 --> 15:42.608
And Ray‐‐ he's pretty hopeless,
but God bless you for trying.

15:42.608 --> 15:44.110
And then Elle wants in

15:44.110 --> 15:47.196
and that lady at the teddy‐bear
factory when I was 5.

15:47.196 --> 15:50.992
Okay...JJ and Ray,
I remember more clearly.

15:50.992 --> 15:53.870
Well, I think it is
a perfectly lovely bear.

15:55.621 --> 15:57.415
Are you not here
with a child?

16:00.376 --> 16:02.003
I get it, okay?

16:02.003 --> 16:03.671
Everyone needs
a piece of you.

16:03.671 --> 16:05.298
It's my job
to stay out of the way.

16:05.298 --> 16:06.591
Why is it your job?

16:06.591 --> 16:07.967
<i>Someone's</i> got to do it.

16:07.967 --> 16:09.385
Not you.

16:09.385 --> 16:11.095
Darling,
I know you were easy.

16:11.095 --> 16:12.972
I didn't know
you were <i>trying</i> to be.

16:12.972 --> 16:14.891
It's not a big deal, Mom.

16:14.891 --> 16:16.726
I know
you have other people

16:16.726 --> 16:18.394
and their dumb stuff
to deal with.

16:18.394 --> 16:19.979
I take care of myself.

16:21.522 --> 16:24.358
But that's why I wanted
to be alone today with you ‐‐

16:24.358 --> 16:26.360
so <i>my</i> dumb stuff
would come first.

16:27.987 --> 16:29.697
Come with me.

16:33.075 --> 16:34.744
Yes! Girl's size 6!

16:36.037 --> 16:37.455
For my sister.

16:37.455 --> 16:39.165
Shouldn't matter what you think,
but it does. I'm sorry.

16:43.669 --> 16:45.046
What are you doing?

16:45.046 --> 16:46.714
Uh, buying these
and then selling them

16:46.714 --> 16:48.257
for a nice profit online.

16:48.257 --> 16:50.468
No, I'm getting those
for my sister.

16:50.468 --> 16:51.719
I'll take a look
at your bid.

16:51.719 --> 16:54.472
Hit me up
at sneakerperv.biz.

16:54.472 --> 16:56.432
That's such a bad name.

16:56.432 --> 16:58.726
Hey, I had those first.

16:58.726 --> 17:00.019
What are you gonna do
about it?

17:01.729 --> 17:04.023
Please ‐‐ go to
the Maple Avenue store!

17:04.023 --> 17:05.191
Your brother's waiting
for you!

17:05.191 --> 17:07.360
[ Sighs ]

17:07.360 --> 17:08.945
So, now that I'm 13,

17:08.945 --> 17:11.030
am I supposed to be
too old for this?

17:11.030 --> 17:12.573
No. 'Cause then
<i>I'd</i> have to be.

17:12.573 --> 17:14.659
Good.
Because I'm having fun.

17:14.659 --> 17:15.701
Me too.

17:17.662 --> 17:19.747
Oh, excuse me.
You're out of green eyeballs.

17:19.747 --> 17:21.582
Oh. I'm sorry.

17:21.582 --> 17:23.167
I'm just distracted
today.

17:23.167 --> 17:24.502
My boyfriend's
going off to college,

17:24.502 --> 17:25.795
and I think this is
the end of every‐‐

17:25.795 --> 17:29.674
Sweetheart, a little less lip,
a little more eyeballs.

17:30.967 --> 17:32.009
Okay.

17:33.678 --> 17:35.680
We'll just let him wink
till she gets back.

17:35.680 --> 17:37.974
[ Both laugh ]

17:40.685 --> 17:43.271
I had them,
but that jerk took them.

17:46.190 --> 17:47.858
"Take them back.

17:47.858 --> 17:50.152
Sometimes
you've got to be bold."

17:50.152 --> 17:51.696
Yeah ‐‐ with <i>small</i> guys.

17:54.699 --> 17:57.285
"You have our shoes."

17:57.285 --> 17:59.036
I paid for these.

17:59.036 --> 18:00.162
We'll pay.

18:00.162 --> 18:04.959
Or do we have
a P‐R‐‐ problem here?"

18:04.959 --> 18:09.005
<i>I</i> don't think we have
a P‐R problem here.

18:09.005 --> 18:12.758
"Give him the shoes,
or I'll kick your ass."

18:12.758 --> 18:13.759
What did you say?

18:13.759 --> 18:15.803
<i>He</i> said it!
He's the sayer!

18:15.803 --> 18:18.472
"He won't hit a guy
in a wheelchair."

18:18.472 --> 18:20.057
Or his brother!

18:20.057 --> 18:21.559
That last part was me.

18:21.559 --> 18:23.269
That's the kind of stuff
<i>I</i> say ‐‐

18:23.269 --> 18:25.813
nice stuff, calm stuff.

18:25.813 --> 18:28.232
I'm not hitting anyone,
okay, kid?

18:28.232 --> 18:29.108
[ Dog whines ]

18:29.108 --> 18:31.360
I got my shoes.
I'm leaving.

18:32.320 --> 18:34.280
Hey!

18:34.280 --> 18:37.074
"Have you met my dog?"

18:38.826 --> 18:40.661
[ Dog barking ]

18:43.289 --> 18:45.207
Maybe you should just...
let him go.

18:47.501 --> 18:50.504
Don't! [ Laughs nervously ]
I'll sell you the shoes.

18:50.504 --> 18:52.381
Here. Take them.

18:52.381 --> 18:54.258
[ Barking continues ]

18:54.258 --> 18:55.259
[ Barking stops ]

18:55.259 --> 18:56.761
Thank you.

18:56.761 --> 18:58.304
Not sure
what just happened,

18:58.304 --> 18:59.972
but I'm happy
to return the favor.

19:01.307 --> 19:02.975
Come on, sweetie.
[ Dog whines ]

19:04.268 --> 19:05.728
"Big day.

19:05.728 --> 19:09.398
Your big brother
taught you to be bold,

19:09.398 --> 19:12.902
taught you
to be kind to strangers."

19:12.902 --> 19:13.986
Yeah, you did.

19:15.404 --> 19:17.365
Mom and Dad
aren't gonna believe this.

19:18.699 --> 19:23.287
"Then big brother taught you
to shut the H‐E" ‐‐

19:23.287 --> 19:25.206
Yep. All right. Got it.

19:28.250 --> 19:29.835
Sweet! Thanks, guys.

19:31.712 --> 19:33.589
You've served me well,
old friends.

19:35.758 --> 19:37.051
The new ones
didn't see that, right?

19:38.094 --> 19:39.553
Taste test, anyone?

19:39.553 --> 19:41.222
If you try Kenneth's,
you can try it twice ‐‐

19:41.222 --> 19:42.848
once going down

19:42.848 --> 19:44.266
and then once a few seconds
later, coming back up.

19:44.266 --> 19:46.352
Yeah, well,
I'm gonna take the high road.

19:46.352 --> 19:48.854
His tastes like
straight up doo‐doo.

19:48.854 --> 19:50.481
Wow. That's ‐‐
That's a solid burn.

19:50.481 --> 19:52.274
Yeah. [ Laughs ]
Oh, I was talking
about his brisket.

19:52.274 --> 19:55.152
Did you guys spend
the entire day barbecuing

19:55.152 --> 19:56.320
and insulting each other?

19:56.320 --> 19:57.655
Mm. Can you tell
by his red eyes?

19:57.655 --> 20:00.074
Oh! I cried <i>once.</i>
It was the smoke!

20:00.074 --> 20:01.492
You guys,
you found your thing ‐‐

20:01.492 --> 20:02.868
being awful to each other.

20:02.868 --> 20:04.662
Trash‐talking's
what you have in common.

20:04.662 --> 20:05.996
Oh.

20:05.996 --> 20:07.957
That's...true.

20:07.957 --> 20:10.084
It wasn't awkward or weird.
We talked the whole time.

20:10.084 --> 20:11.794
Oh, my God.
We sure did.

20:11.794 --> 20:14.797
We filled each silence
with a stream of hateful barbs.

20:14.797 --> 20:15.881
[ Chuckles ]
I could do that all day long.

20:15.881 --> 20:17.550
Yeah!

20:17.550 --> 20:19.218
That shirt is stupid.
No wonder you're still single.

20:19.218 --> 20:20.970
Uh‐huh, yeah. Well,
I'd rather be single than ‐‐

20:20.970 --> 20:22.304
Than what, Kenneth?

20:22.304 --> 20:23.472
Then I'd better get going.
